---
export const squidoc = {
  title: "Squidoc",
  description: "Static docs with a plugin system, versioning, and themeable pages.",
};
---

<section class="sq-home-hero">
  <div class="sq-home-hero__inner">
    <div class="sq-home-hero__copy">
      <h1>Documentation that starts as Markdown and stays yours.</h1>
      <p>
        Squidoc generates a static docs site with a real plugin system, theme contracts, versioned
        docs, custom pages, and sensible SEO defaults. Start with files on disk. Add power when the
        docs actually need it.
      </p>
      <div class="sq-home-hero__actions">
        <a class="sq-home-button sq-home-button--primary" href="/docs/getting-started">
          Start building
        </a>
        <a class="sq-home-button sq-home-button--secondary" href="/docs/plugins">
          Explore plugins
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="sq-home-terminal" aria-label="Create a Squidoc project">
      <div class="sq-home-terminal__bar">
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
      </div>
      <pre><code>npm create squidoc@latest my-docs
cd my-docs
npm run dev

# add docs
docs/
  index.md
  guides/plugins.md
  versions/0.1/configuration.md</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sq-home-section sq-home-start">
  <div class="sq-home-section__heading">
    <h2>What you get from the first command</h2>
    <p>
      A Squidoc project is deliberately plain: Markdown files, one config file, static output, and
      packages you can replace as your site grows.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="sq-home-start__grid">
    <div class="sq-home-file-tree" aria-label="Generated project structure">
      <p>my-docs/</p>
      <ul>
        <li>docs/index.md</li>
        <li>docs/getting-started.md</li>
        <li>pages/index.astro</li>
        <li>public/squidoc-logo.svg</li>
        <li>docs.config.ts</li>
        <li>package.json</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="sq-home-config">
      <pre><code>import &#123; defineConfig &#125; from "squidoc";

export default defineConfig(&#123;
  site: &#123;
    name: "My Docs",
    url: "https://docs.example.com",
  &#125;,
  docs: &#123;
    basePath: "/docs",
  &#125;,
  theme: &#123;
    name: "@squidoc/theme-basic",
    options: &#123;
      primaryColor: "#4a54df",
    &#125;,
  &#125;,
&#125;);</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sq-home-section sq-home-defaults">
  <div class="sq-home-section__heading">
    <h2>The default site is already useful</h2>
    <p>
      The starter includes the pieces most docs sites need on day one. They are plugins, so teams can
      remove them, configure them, or replace them later.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="sq-home-defaults__list">
    <article>
      <h3>Search</h3>
      <p>Builds a static search index and keeps versioned results labeled.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Code blocks</h3>
      <p>Adds syntax highlighting and copy buttons without forcing authors to write markup.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Article tree</h3>
      <p>Shows headings on long pages and tracks the active section while readers scroll.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>SEO</h3>
      <p>Outputs canonical tags, metadata, sitemap, robots rules, and social tags.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Pages</h3>
      <p>Lets teams build homepages, changelogs, and custom landing pages with Astro.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Versions</h3>
      <p>Keeps old docs available when APIs or configuration change between releases.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sq-home-section sq-home-split">
  <div>
    <h2>Markdown first. Astro when you need more.</h2>
    <p>
      Most docs can stay as Markdown. When a page needs a custom layout, a chart, a product
      comparison, or a launch page, the pages plugin lets you write an Astro page and choose the
      stable page or docs layout.
    </p>
    <a href="/docs/pages">Read the pages guide</a>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h2>Themes own structure, not just colors.</h2>
    <p>
      Themes can move navigation, change headers and footers, decide where plugin UI appears, and
      provide separate layouts for docs and standalone pages. Squidoc keeps the layout contract
      small so theme authors know what to support.
    </p>
    <a href="/docs/theme-authoring">Read the theme guide</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="sq-home-section sq-home-flow">
  <div class="sq-home-section__heading">
    <h2>The path to production is boring on purpose</h2>
    <p>
      Squidoc builds static files. That means previews are easy, CI is predictable, and the final
      artifact can go almost anywhere.
    </p>
  </div>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>Write docs</strong>
      <span>Add Markdown under <code>docs/</code>, or custom Astro pages under <code>pages/</code>.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Run checks</strong>
      <span>Use <code>squidoc check</code> and browser smoke tests before publishing.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Build static output</strong>
      <span><code>squidoc build</code> produces the files your host needs.</span>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Deploy</strong>
      <span>Ship to Vercel, Netlify, Cloudflare Pages, GitHub Pages, Docker, or S3.</span>
    </li>
  </ol>
</section>

<section class="sq-home-section sq-home-close">
  <h2>Build the docs site first. Customize it when the work asks for it.</h2>
  <div class="sq-home-close__actions">
    <a class="sq-home-button sq-home-button--primary" href="/docs/getting-started">
      Get started
    </a>
    <a class="sq-home-button sq-home-button--secondary" href="/docs/configuration">
      View configuration
    </a>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sq-home-hero {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--squidoc-border);
    background:
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgb(74 84 223 / 7%) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(0deg, rgb(74 84 223 / 7%) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(135deg, rgb(83 183 254 / 13%), transparent 38%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #f8fbff 0%, #ffffff 80%);
    background-size:
      44px 44px,
      44px 44px,
      auto,
      auto;
  }

  .sq-home-hero::before {
    position: absolute;
    inset: auto 0 0;
    height: 180px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, #ffffff);
    content: "";
  }

  .sq-home-hero__inner,
  .sq-home-section {
    width: min(1120px, calc(100% - 48px));
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .sq-home-hero__inner {
    position: relative;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(360px, 470px);
    gap: 56px;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 92px 0 88px;
  }

  .sq-home-hero h1,
  .sq-home-section h2,
  .sq-home-section h3,
  .sq-home-hero p,
  .sq-home-section p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sq-home-hero h1 {
    max-width: 760px;
    color: var(--squidoc-text);
    font-size: clamp(50px, 7.6vw, 92px);
    line-height: 0.94;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .sq-home-hero__copy p {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-top: 28px;
    color: var(--squidoc-muted);
    font-size: 21px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .sq-home-hero__actions,
  .sq-home-close__actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .sq-home-button {
    display: inline-flex;
    min-height: 44px;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0 17px;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .sq-home-button--primary {
    color: #ffffff;
    background: var(--squidoc-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 24px rgb(74 84 223 / 18%);
  }

  .sq-home-button--secondary {
    border: 1px solid var(--squidoc-border);
    color: var(--squidoc-text);
    background: rgb(255 255 255 / 82%);
  }

  .sq-home-terminal,
  .sq-home-config {
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid #1e293b;
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: #111827;
    box-shadow: 0 26px 60px rgb(23 32 51 / 18%);
  }

  .sq-home-terminal__bar {
    display: flex;
    gap: 7px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(255 255 255 / 8%);
    padding: 13px 16px;
    background: #0f172a;
  }

  .sq-home-terminal__bar span {
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: #64748b;
  }

  .sq-home-terminal pre,
  .sq-home-config pre {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 22px;
    overflow: auto;
    color: #dbeafe;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .sq-home-section {
    padding: 76px 0;
  }

  .sq-home-section + .sq-home-section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--squidoc-border);
  }

  .sq-home-section__heading {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-bottom: 34px;
  }

  .sq-home-section h2 {
    color: var(--squidoc-text);
    font-size: clamp(34px, 4.4vw, 54px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .sq-home-section__heading p,
  .sq-home-split p,
  .sq-home-flow span {
    margin-top: 16px;
    color: var(--squidoc-muted);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .sq-home-start__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(250px, 0.55fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 18px;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .sq-home-file-tree,
  .sq-home-defaults__list article,
  .sq-home-split > div,
  .sq-home-flow li,
  .sq-home-close {
    border: 1px solid var(--squidoc-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: #ffffff;
  }

  .sq-home-file-tree {
    padding: 24px;
    color: var(--squidoc-text);
    font-family:
      "SFMono-Regular", Consolas, "Liberation Mono", Menlo, monospace;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .sq-home-file-tree p {
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .sq-home-file-tree ul {
    margin: 8px 0 0;
    padding-left: 22px;
    color: var(--squidoc-muted);
  }

  .sq-home-defaults__list {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
  }

  .sq-home-defaults__list article {
    min-height: 150px;
    padding: 22px;
  }

  .sq-home-defaults__list h3,
  .sq-home-split h2 {
    color: var(--squidoc-text);
    font-size: 21px;
  }

  .sq-home-defaults__list p {
    margin-top: 10px;
    color: var(--squidoc-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .sq-home-split {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .sq-home-split > div {
    padding: 30px;
  }

  .sq-home-split a {
    display: inline-flex;
    margin-top: 22px;
    color: var(--squidoc-accent);
    font-weight: 800;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .sq-home-flow ol {
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    counter-reset: steps;
  }

  .sq-home-flow li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 54px minmax(160px, 0.38fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 18px;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 20px;
    counter-increment: steps;
  }

  .sq-home-flow li::before {
    display: inline-grid;
    width: 42px;
    height: 42px;
    place-items: center;
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: #ffffff;
    background: var(--squidoc-accent);
    content: counter(steps);
    font-weight: 900;
  }

  .sq-home-flow strong {
    color: var(--squidoc-text);
    font-size: 18px;
  }

  .sq-home-flow span {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 16px;
  }

  .sq-home-flow code {
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 0.08em 0.28em;
    color: #334155;
    background: #f8fafc;
    font-size: 0.92em;
  }

  .sq-home-close {
    margin-bottom: 76px;
    padding: 42px;
    background:
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgb(74 84 223 / 7%) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(0deg, rgb(74 84 223 / 7%) 1px, transparent 1px),
      #ffffff;
    background-size: 36px 36px;
  }

  .sq-home-close h2 {
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .sq-home-hero__inner,
    .sq-home-start__grid,
    .sq-home-split {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .sq-home-defaults__list {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .sq-home-hero__inner,
    .sq-home-section {
      width: calc(100% - 32px);
    }

    .sq-home-hero__inner {
      padding: 62px 0;
    }

    .sq-home-hero h1 {
      font-size: 44px;
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
    }

    .sq-home-hero__copy p,
    .sq-home-section__heading p,
    .sq-home-split p {
      font-size: 17px;
    }

    .sq-home-section {
      padding: 54px 0;
    }

    .sq-home-defaults__list,
    .sq-home-flow li {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .sq-home-flow li {
      align-items: start;
    }

    .sq-home-close {
      margin-bottom: 54px;
      padding: 28px;
    }
  }
</style>
